# Desktop shell UI

Authoritative detail: `specs/design/desktop-shell-patterns.md`.

## Resizable columns

- Main **Vault** / **Episodes** / **editor** workspace (**`MainWorkspaceSplit`**): uses **`DesktopHorizontalSplit`** for width; when **both** Vault and Episodes are open, **`DesktopVerticalSplit`** stacks them in the left column (**`vaultEpisodesStack.topHeightPx`** in **`layoutPanelsV4`**). **One** main **left column width** (persisted as **`inbox.leftWidthPx`**, mirrored to **`podcastsMain.leftWidthPx`**); **editor** is **`flex: 1`**. Do **not** reintroduce **`react-resizable-panels`** for this main split without a spec update (it used percentage remapping and caused visible **1px jitter** on window resize). Persist widths and stack height via **`layoutStore`** (`layoutPanelsV4`).

## Editor Toolbar

- The **Editor Toolbar** is **`EditorWorkspaceToolbar`**: full-width chrome **above** **`MainWorkspaceSplit`** and the notifications column (**inside** **`VaultTab`**, before **`DesktopHorizontalSplitEnd`**). It includes the **Vault** toggle, **Back / Forward**, compose title + **Cancel** when composing, and the **notifications** toggle. Icons use **`@radix-ui/react-icons`** at **15×15** inside **`pane-header-add-btn__glyph`**. Markup: **`pane-header pane-header--editor-toolbar`**; styles: **`.pane-header--editor-toolbar`**, **`.pane-header-add-btn`**, and pressed accents in **`App.css`**. Open-note tabs render in **`WindowTitleBar`**, not in this row.

## Cursors

- Treat the desktop UI as a **desktop app**: **`cursor: default`** on **buttons**, **rail tabs**, **list rows**, and similar chrome. **Do not** use **`cursor: pointer`** for those.
- **Disabled** elements: **no** **`cursor: not-allowed`**; keep **`cursor: default`** with existing opacity / color disabled styling.
- **Exception:** **Panel separators** keep **`col-resize` / `row-resize`** (and any other explicit resize affordances).
- **Exception:** **Today Hub** read-only cell preview (`.today-hub-canvas__cell-readonly` / `.today-hub-canvas__cell-static-rich`) uses **`cursor: text`**; links inside still use pointer from markdown token CSS.
